title: DataCore SANsymphony: Pool Status
agents: datacore_rest
catalog: storage/datacore
license: GPLv2
distribution: andre_eckstein
description:
 This check monitors the status and performance of storage pools in a
 DataCore SANsymphony storage system. Storage pools aggregate physical
 disks to provide capacity for virtual disks.

 The check monitors:

 - Pool running status
 - Oversubscription state (configurable: {CRIT}, {WARN}, or ignore)
 - Read and write IOPS
 - Read and write throughput
 - Read and write latency
 - Read/write ratio
 - Pool member information

 The check returns {CRIT} if the pool is not running, and the configured
 state for oversubscription conditions.

 This check requires the special agent configurable through
 "DataCore SANsymphony via REST API".

item:
 The name (Alias) of the storage pool.

discovery:
 One service is created for each storage pool.
